<br>
Use the General's sword in primary and the Centi LS in the offhand. Weapons of delay 24 or higher will hit harder when they hit compared to faster weapons, but the key to the offhand is the ratio i.e. I would still use a 10/23 over a 10/24.<br>
<br>
For your offhand also look at what stats it gives you like HPs Dex and or resists. Even with the AA skill Ambidexterity the primary hand does most of the damage. Once again the Centi Longsword has +8 Str and +8 Stamina. That is pretty nice on a warrior and the Centi is probably cheaper than other upgrades.<br>
